The term '''registered owner''' is usually used in instances of [[title (property)|title]] of a vehicle (such as an automobile) to refer to the person who has ''right of possession'' of the vehicle, as opposed to the party that has ''right of property''.  The party that has right of property is referred to as a [[lienholder]], and in the event the registered owner fails to pay off the lien according to the agreed-to terms, the lienholder has the right to invoke [[repossession]] of the vehicle.

