The '''Seneschal of the Agenais''' was an officer carrying out and managing the domestic affairs of the lord of the former county and district of [[Agenais]]. During the course of the twelfth century, the [[seneschal]]ship, also became an office of military command.
The seneschal managed the household, coordinating between the receivers of various landholdings and the chamber, treasury, and the chancellory or chapel. The seneschals of the Agenais, like those appointed in [[Seneschal of Périgord|Périgord]], [[Seneschal of Poitou|Poitou]], and [[Seneschal of Anjou|Najou]] had custody of demesne fortresses, the regional treasuries, and presidency of the highest court of regional custom.
